      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Alaaraaf</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>Don't turn around, that wastes too much time - just wait a little bit longer before casting, after a while, you'll automatically wait a tiny bit after "stopping" to begin casting yout spells.</P><P><font size=1><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=54401" target="_blank">Azumaan</a></b><br>33 Erudite Necromancer<br>Silver Faith<br>Mithaniel Marr</font id=size1><BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Actually, there is a big ol' plus to turning, at least a little bit...</P><P>There was a post ages and ages ago on the developer's forums, relating to this.  What happens is that the server only updates your position every so often.  If you're running and you stop, although you have stopped, the server doesn't know this.  So, it gueses where you should be, based on where you appeared to be running.  </P><P>Because of this, when you finish casting, you're not where the server thought you were when you started.  So, it thinks you moved and the spell fails.</P><P>When you turn, even a fraction, this forces the server to update your position.  So, all you have to do, is tap left, or right, when you stop and the problem is fixed.</P><P>The post is probably still buried away in the dev boards, if you wanna go look for it, but I can't be bothered.  Alternatively, try the turning thing and you can see for yourself the difference it makes.</P><P>AlAaraaf.</P><P><BR> </font></td>
